          "date": "2013-07-01 15:15:05.000000000",
          "tz": 120
        },
        "subject": "LU-3504 libcfs: alloc kmem atomic when owning resource lr_lock",
        "message": "LU-3504 libcfs: alloc kmem atomic when owning resource lr_lock\n\nThis change fixes a regression introduced by the following commit:\n    commit 2c7a41a5c5958d36fa839ea91f3e63375cbd90fc\n    Author: Vitaly Fertman <vitaly_fertman@xyratex.com>\n    Date:   Tue Jun 26 01:47:50 2012 +0400\n        LU-1157 ldlm: replace waiting flock lists by hashes\n\nThis commit introduced the possibility of a dead-lock which\ncan occur on MDS handling 1st FLock request for an export,\nowning resource lr_lock spin-lock from lock_res_and_lock()\nthe kmem allocation of the new hashing stuff for FLocks is\nnot done atomic and thus can resched() allowing competitor\nthreads to spin forever on all available CPUs.\n\nThe fix is to force all related kmem allocs to be done\natomically.\n\nSigned-off-by: Bruno Faccini <bruno.faccini@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I9f2f4368e69f69c27a6e952126d71ddd7d7f7d43\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
